.TH PROSE 1 "February 2026" "prose 1.17.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
prose \- a vim-inspired text editor for prose writing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B prose
.RI [ file ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B prose
is a modal text editor inspired by vim, designed specifically for writing prose. It features real-time British English spell checking, multiple file support with tabs, Markdown syntax highlighting, and vim-like navigation and editing commands.
.PP
prose operates in three main modes:
.TP
.B Default Mode
For navigation and text manipulation. This is the initial mode.
.TP
.B Edit Mode
For inserting and editing text (entered with
.BR i ,
.BR o ,
.BR O ,
or
.BR A ).
.TP
.B Line-Select Mode
For selecting and operating on entire lines (entered with
.BR V ).
.SH MODES
.SS Default Mode
The primary mode for navigation and issuing commands. Press
.B Esc
from any other mode to return to Default mode.
.SS Edit Mode
Insert and edit text freely. Press
.B Esc
to return to Default mode. Press
.B Enter
to create a new line.
.SS Line-Select Mode
Select entire lines for deletion or yanking. Use
.B j
and
.B k
to extend the selection. Press
.B Esc
to return to Default mode.
.SH NAVIGATION
.SS Basic Movement (Default Mode)
.TP
.BR h ", " j ", " k ", " l
Move left, down, up, right (vim-style)
.TP
.BR "Arrow Keys"
Also work in Default and Edit modes
.TP
.BR "Home" ", " "End"
Jump to start or end of line
.TP
.BR ^
Jump to first non-whitespace character on line
.TP
.BR $
Jump to end of line
.TP
.BR w
Jump to the start of the next word
.TP
.BR b
Jump to the start of the previous word
.TP
.B gg
Jump to first line of document
.TP
.B G
Jump to last line of document
.TP
.BR "Ctrl-U" ", " "Page Up"
Scroll up by one window height
.TP
.BR "Ctrl-D" ", " "Page Down"
Scroll down by one window height
.TP
.BR "Shift-Page Up"
Jump to first line (same as gg)
.TP
.BR "Shift-Page Down"
Jump to last line (same as G)
.TP
.B Mouse Click
Position cursor at click location
.SS Spell Check Navigation (Default Mode)
.TP
.B x
Jump to next spelling error
.TP
.B X
Jump to previous spelling error
.SS Search Navigation (Default Mode)
.TP
.B /
Enter search mode. Type search term and press Enter to highlight matches
.TP
.B //
Clear current search (double tap)
.TP
.B n
Jump to next search match
.TP
.B N
Jump to previous search match
.SH EDITING
.SS Entering Edit Mode
.TP
.B i
Enter Edit mode at cursor position
.TP
.B A
Move to end of line and enter Edit mode
.TP
.B o
Insert new line below cursor and enter Edit mode
.TP
.B O
Insert new line above cursor and enter Edit mode
.SS Deleting Text (Default Mode)
.TP
.B dd
Delete current line
.TP
.B Del
In Edit mode, delete character after cursor
.TP
.B Backspace
In Edit mode, delete character before cursor
.SS Line-Select Operations
.TP
.B V
Enter Line-Select mode at current line
.TP
.BR j ", " k " (in Line-Select)"
Extend selection down or up
.TP
.BR d " (in Line-Select)"
Delete selected lines
.TP
.BR y " (in Line-Select)"
Yank (copy) selected lines
.SS Yank and Paste (Default Mode)
.TP
.B yy
Yank (copy) current line
.TP
.BR y " (in Line-Select)"
Yank selected lines
.TP
.B p
Paste yanked text below current line
.TP
.B P
Paste yanked text above current line
.SS Send Lines
.TP
.B ss
Send current line to external buffer
.TP
.BR s " (in Line-Select)"
Send selected lines to external buffer
.SS Undo and Redo (Default Mode)
.TP
.B u
Undo last change
.TP
.B Ctrl-R
Redo previously undone change
.SH SPELL CHECKING
.B prose
includes real-time British English spell checking for Markdown (.md, .markdown) and text (.txt) files.
Spell checking is
.B off by default
and can be toggled using the
.B :spell
command. When enabled, misspelled words are highlighted, and spelling errors can be navigated using
.B x
(next error) and
.B X
(previous error).
.PP
The spell checker:
.IP \(bu 2
Uses a comprehensive British English dictionary
.IP \(bu 2
Skips short words (1-2 letters)
.IP \(bu 2
Ignores all-uppercase words (acronyms like API, HTTP)
.IP \(bu 2
Supports contractions (don't, can't, won't)
.IP \(bu 2
Accepts British spellings (colour, honour, organise, centre, theatre)
.SH SEARCHING
.TP
.B /
Enter search mode. The status bar prompts for a search term.
.TP
.B Enter
Execute search. Matching text is highlighted throughout the document.
.TP
.B Esc
Cancel search entry.
.TP
.B //
Clear current search highlights (double tap slash).
.TP
.B n
Jump to next search match.
.TP
.B N
Jump to previous search match.
.PP
The search displays a match counter (e.g., "4 matches") in the status bar while active.
.SH BUFFERS AND TABS
.B prose
supports multiple files in tabs. Each file is loaded into a buffer.
.SS Tab Navigation
.TP
.B Tab
Switch to next tab
.TP
.B Shift-Tab
Switch to previous tab
.SS Special Buffers
.TP
.B S
Jump to scratch buffer (creates it if it doesn't exist). The scratch buffer is a temporary workspace that persists for the session but is not saved to disk.
.SH FILE OPERATIONS
.SS Opening Files
.TP
.B Space-O
Open directory browser. Navigate with arrow keys or
.BR j / k ,
press
.B Enter
to open file,
.B b
to open in new tab, or
.B Esc
to cancel.
.SS Saving and Quitting
.TP
.B :w
Write (save) current file
.TP
.B :q
Quit current buffer/tab
.TP
.B :q!
Force quit without saving
.TP
.B :wq
Write and quit
.TP
.B :qa
Quit all buffers (prompts if unsaved changes)
.TP
.B :qa!
Force quit all without saving
.TP
.B :wqa
Write all modified buffers and quit all
.TP
.B :qwa
Alias for :wqa
.SS File Management
.TP
.BI :rename " newname"
Rename/move current file to
.I newname
.SS Spell Checking
.TP
.B :spell
Toggle spell checking on/off. Spell checking is off by default and only works for Markdown (.md, .markdown) and text (.txt) files.
.SH MARKDOWN SUPPORT
.SS Syntax Highlighting
Markdown files (.md, .markdown) receive syntax highlighting for:
.IP \(bu 2
Headers (# ## ###)
.IP \(bu 2
Bold and italic text
.IP \(bu 2
Code blocks and inline code
.IP \(bu 2
Links and images
.IP \(bu 2
Lists
.SS Document Outline
.TP
.B Space-H
Open Markdown document outline (Markdown files only). Shows all headers in a floating overlay. Navigate with arrow keys or
.BR j / k ,
press
.B Enter
to jump to header, or
.B Esc
to cancel.
.SH KEY BINDINGS SUMMARY
.SS Leader Key
.B Space
is the leader key for special commands:
.TP
.B Space-O
Open directory browser
.TP
.B Space-H
Open document outline (Markdown only)
.TP
.B Space--
Adjust column width. Use left/right arrow keys (or h/l) to decrease/increase
the text column width. Press Enter to confirm or Escape to cancel and revert.
Minimum width is 20 characters; maximum is the terminal width.
.SS Command Mode
.TP
.B :
Enter command mode to issue file operations (w, q, wq, qa, etc.)
.SS Search Mode
.TP
.B /
Enter search mode
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B prose
currently has no configuration file. All behaviour is built-in.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.prose/
Reserved for future configuration and data files (not currently used)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
No environment variables are used by
.BR prose .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B prose
Start
.B prose
with an empty scratch buffer.
.TP
.B prose README.md
Open README.md for editing.
.TP
.B prose *.txt
Open all .txt files in the current directory, each in its own tab.
.TP
.B prose chapter1.md chapter2.md notes.txt
Open multiple files in tabs.
.SH WORD DEFINITION
For word-based navigation (
.B w
and
.B b
commands),
.B prose
uses a Vim-style word definition: sequences of letters, digits, and underscores. This means:
.IP \(bu 2
.B hello_world
is one word
.IP \(bu 2
.B hello-world
is two words (hyphen separates)
.IP \(bu 2
.B test123
is one word
